This paper is about zero-shot learning (ZSL) using a generative model-based approach. The focus is on learning feature-to-feature translator networks using alternating back-propagation. This involves mapping class features and a latent vector to image features. The paper discusses the use of a single conditional generator that is trained using maximum likelihood estimation. Given that the paper is about computer vision and machine learning, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other possible sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.MM (Multimedia).
